        <abstract> 
<p>CD disappointed in Pusey’s sermon against evolution [<hi rend="italic">Un-science, not science, adverse to faith</hi> (1878), sermon read by H. P. Liddon at St Mary’s, Oxford, on 3 Nov 1878]. Does not agree that religion and science can be kept as distant as Pusey desires. Geology and biology must deal with history of earth and of man. But that is no reason for bitter hostility.</p> 
        </abstract>
